The paper proposes a novel autoregressive architecture for modeling temporal sequences of multi-relational graphs, which is a problem that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The use of recurrent neural networks and the focus on modeling joint probability distributions suggest that cs.AI and cs.LG are likely sub-categories. The use of graph data and the focus on link prediction suggest that cs.DB and cs.SI are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the use of natural language processing techniques for evaluating the proposed method suggests that cs.CL is a possible sub-category as well.
